ABUJA (SundiataPost) – One of Nigeria’s greatest scholars, Prof. Obioha Chima Nwana, 86, is dead. He died on Saturday in Atlanta, Georgia, the United States. O. C. Nwana was formerly the Dean, Faculty of Education, University of Nigeria, Nsukka, UNN. He was the second fellow of the Nigerian Academy of Education (NAE), a height he attained in 1993 after Prof Grace Alele-Williams, who became the first fellow in 1990. He hailed from Arondizogu, in Ideato Local Government Area of  Imo State. The late Prof Nwana was also the son of the late Pita Nwana, who in 1933 without much formal education, wrote Omenuko, the path-breaking Igbo novel, which for several years was a recommended text in secondary schools for Igbo literature. OWERRI (Sundiata Post) - Imo State Governor, Hon. Emeka Ihedioha, has appointed a former member of the House of Representatives, Hon. Uche Onyeaguocha as Secretary to the State Government (SSG).According to a statement signed by the governor's Chief Press Secretary, Chibuike Onyeukwu on Saturday, Ihedioha also approved the appointment of Chief… June 1, 2019 In "Top Stories" By Oluwabukola Akanni   Ibadan   -     The Medical and Dental Council of Nigeria (MDCN) says it is currently investigating not less than 90 medical malpractice petitions filed against some of its members. The Registrar, Dr Tajudeen Sanusi, made this known on Thursday in Ibadan on the sidelines of a Distinguished… July 13, 2018 In "News" By Olasunkanmi Onifade Abuja -   Dr Chito Nwana, the Chairperson, Guild of Medical Directors, FCT chapter, has warned that the use of unsterilised equipment for female genital mutilation could lead to HIV and AIDS. Nwana said this in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Tuesday… February 6, 2018 In "Health"